  "text": "Structured and intense synoptic activity appears also in PC 3 (Fig. 18) . It comes from the Atlantic and affects the northern side of the domain, as was already clear from the geopotential standard deviation composites (Fig. 14c) . No clear enhancement of the perturbations takes place along the journey of the perturbations through the area. This time, the perturbations travel about 5°(600 km) to the north with respect to the extreme PC 1 + case. The previous results are consistent with significant vertical movements in the low levels of the troposphere. Fig. 19 shows that during high phases of PC 1 , upward velocities occur over the Iberian Peninsula. PC 2 is clearly linked to rising air over the eastern Mediterranean and subsidence over the Iberian Peninsula [CITATION_1] . Finally, PC 3 shows significant vertical movements over the northern part of the domain, consistent with topographic forcing, as reflected by the clear relationship between the topography and the spatial structure of the EOF. ",
